reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great phone for teenagers
reviews.reviewText: Looks great, slim thickness, has a case, large screen size, okay camera, user friendly, easy to navigate, overall a hreat buy for the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great phone for standard users
reviews.reviewText: This phone is perfect for me or anyone who just needs a standard reliable cell. It's not going to win any awards for speed or gaming but it is very easy to use and does exactly what I need it to, basic web surfing text and calling. Worth the money.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for the money
reviews.reviewText: Easy to set up and gets the job done

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Value Phone for Tello Too
reviews.reviewText: I was looking for a cheap backup phone to work with Tello, and this is it. I like everything about it with the possible exception of how hard it was for me to figure out how to turn it off. You have to use the pull down quick menu, and then it's in the lower right hand corner. The battery life is long, the charge time is pretty fast, the sound is decent, as is the call quality. It was very easy to set up, too. I don't think you can go wrong with this one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars All around great budget phone
reviews.reviewText: Bought as a gift for a teenager. She absolutely loved it. Has excellent capabilities for calling, texting, youtube, netflix, and sending emails. The camera blew me away and was much better than expected. Do not expect this phone to beat a brand new Samsung or Iphone but competes as a mid range phone.
